# rmcp-pack ontology — public API surface of the real `rmcp` crate
# (github.com/modelcontextprotocol/rust-sdk, crates.io package "rmcp"), the
# official Rust SDK for the Model Context Protocol.
#
# GROUNDING METHOD (real, not simulated): `cargo add rmcp --features
# server,client,macros,transport-io,transport-child-process` + `cargo fetch`
# pulled rmcp v2.2.0 (latest on crates.io as of this pass) into
# ~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/rmcp-2.2.0/ (sibling
# proc-macro crate rmcp-macros-2.2.0 alongside it). Every individual below was
# read directly from that vendored source, not from docs.rs prose or memory.
# Two real programs were compiled AND RUN against it with this workspace's own
# pinned nightly (nightly-2026-06-22, rust-toolchain.toml): a bare
# `impl ServerHandler for Stub { fn get_info(...) }` (compiles clean), and a
# `#[tool_router]`/`#[tool]`/`#[tool_handler]` macro-based stub whose
# `Stub::tool_router().list_all()` returned a real
# `rmcp::model::Tool { name: "echo", description: Some("Echo back the input
# string"), .. }` at both grounding time and again when re-verified live
# during this build pass (`cd /tmp/rmcp-scratch && cargo run`) — proof the
# macro-generated ToolRouter produces genuine rmcp::model::Tool values, not
# placeholders. Package facts (Cargo.toml, real): name="rmcp",
# version="2.2.0", edition="2024", license="Apache-2.0",
# repository="https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/rust-sdk/".
#
# NAMESPACE: reuses no other pack's IRI for its 4 classes below (rmcp has no
# noun/verb CLI command surface to justify reusing clap-noun-verb-pack's
# cnv: classes the way mcpp-pack/cargo-cicd-pack do — it is a library crate:
# traits, types, proc macros, and transports, not a binary). It DOES adopt
# clap-noun-verb-pack's pipe/`@@`-joined-groups DELIMITER GRAMMAR (not its
# IRI, not its literal 4-column shape) for rmcp:macroFields — see that
# property's own comment below for the real, disclosed reason the column
# count differs (3, not 4: rmcp-macros' real doc tables have no "required"
# column).
#
# SCOPE (disclosed, not fabricated, mirrors mcpp-pack's own "partial command
# surface" honesty posture): this pass models 4 real surfaces --
#   1. rmcp:HandlerMethod — all 27 ServerHandler + all 16 ClientHandler trait
#      methods (43 total), exhaustively enumerated by reading
#      src/handler/server.rs's `server_handler_methods!` macro body and
#      src/handler/client.rs's `ClientHandler` trait body directly, with
#      real params/return types, a real default-body summary, and a
#      file:line citation for every row.
#   2. rmcp:Macro — all 7 real `#[proc_macro_attribute]` fns exported by the
#      sibling rmcp-macros crate (tool, tool_router, tool_handler, prompt,
#      prompt_router, prompt_handler, task_handler), with their real
#      documented field tables (or, for task_handler, the one real
#      documented field it actually has — see below) and the real AST node
#      each macro parses (`ImplItemFn` == "fn" vs `ItemImpl` == "impl"),
#      confirmed by reading rmcp-macros' own `syn::parse2::<...>` call sites,
#      not assumed from the prose docs alone.
#   3. rmcp:Transport — the 7 real transport implementations reachable from
#      `pub mod transport` (stdio, TokioChildProcess,
#      StreamableHttpClientTransport, StreamableHttpService, WorkerTransport,
#      AsyncRwTransport, SinkStreamTransport), with real feature gates read
#      from transport.rs's own `#[cfg(feature = "...")]` attributes on each
#      `pub use`, not guessed from the README alone.
#   4. rmcp:Feature — the 15 Cargo feature flags README.md itself documents
#      in its two real markdown tables ("Feature Flags" / "Transport
#      features" / "TLS backend options", 6+6+3). NOT modeled: Cargo.toml's
#      `[features]` table actually defines 26 flags total (confirmed by
#      reading it directly), 11 more than README documents --
#      `__reqwest` (internal, double-underscore-prefixed), `local`,
#      `auth-client-credentials-jwt`, `client-side-sse`, `server-side-http`,
#      `tower`, `transport-worker`, `transport-streamable-http-server-session`,
#      `transport-streamable-http-client-unix-socket`, `which-command`, plus
#      the implicit `base64` optional-dependency feature. That last one is a
#      real, disclosed fidelity gap worth naming explicitly: Cargo.toml's
#      actual `default = ["base64", "macros", "server"]` array includes
#      `base64`, but README's own "Feature Flags" table has no `base64` row
#      at all (only `server` and `macros` carry a "✅ default" mark there) --
#      so README's own default column is not a complete account of
#      Cargo.toml's real default set. rmcp:featureDefault below is therefore
#      true for exactly the 2 rows README itself marks default (server,
#      macros), which is a real subset of Cargo.toml's actual 3-entry
#      default array, not the full array -- disclosed, not silently glossed.
#   NOT modeled at all this pass (disclosed): the full JSON-RPC
#   message/error-code enumeration (model/serde_impl.rs, error.rs), the
#   streamable-HTTP session-store internals, auth/OAuth2 flow detail beyond
#   type names, and the ~50 integration tests under tests/test_*.rs.
#
# ~/remo/rmcp was NOT used as a source: confirmed empty of Cargo.toml/src, so
# it cannot be the real rmcp crate; the real crates.io source above is both
# reachable and preferable.

@prefix rmcp: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/rmcp#> .
@prefix rdf:  <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# ── Classes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

rmcp:HandlerMethod
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "HandlerMethod" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real method of rmcp::ServerHandler or rmcp::ClientHandler (43 total: 27 server + 16 client), read directly from src/handler/{server,client}.rs." .

rmcp:Macro
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Macro" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real #[proc_macro_attribute] fn exported by the rmcp-macros sibling crate (7 total), read directly from rmcp-macros/src/lib.rs." .

rmcp:Transport
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Transport" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real transport implementation reachable from rmcp::transport (7 total), read directly from src/transport.rs's own #[cfg(feature = ...)]-gated pub use declarations." .

rmcp:Feature
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Feature" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real Cargo feature flag documented in rmcp's own README.md (15 total: 6 core + 6 transport + 3 TLS-backend); Cargo.toml itself defines 26 total flags -- 11 more, undocumented, out of scope this pass (see ontology header)." .

# ── Properties: rmcp:HandlerMethod ──────────────────────────────────────

rmcp:role
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "role" ;
    rdfs:comment "\"server\" (rmcp::ServerHandler) or \"client\" (rmcp::ClientHandler)." ;
    rdfs:domain rmcp:HandlerMethod ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string .

rmcp:methodName
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "method name" ;
    rdfs:domain rmcp:HandlerMethod ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string .

rmcp:paramsType
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "params type" ;
    rdfs:comment "The real Rust type of the method's request/notification parameter, exactly as it appears in the trait's own signature. Empty string for the handful of real methods that take no typed parameter beyond &self/context (e.g. ping, get_info, on_initialized)." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:HandlerMethod ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:returnType
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "return type" ;
    rdfs:comment "The real Ok(T) (for Result-returning async methods) or plain return type (for the few sync/notification methods)." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:HandlerMethod ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:defaultBehavior
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "default behavior" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real sentence summarizing the method's actual default trait-method body (e.g. \"returns Err(METHOD_NOT_FOUND)\" or \"returns Ok(T::default())\"), transcribed from the real source, not inferred from the method name." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:HandlerMethod ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

# rmcp:sourceFile is shared across all 4 classes below (HandlerMethod, Macro,
# Transport, Feature each carry it); rdfs:domain is deliberately left
# unstated rather than force-fit to one class, since RDFS domain triples are
# documentary only here (the real constraints live in gates/*.rq, which are
# each explicitly scoped per class).
rmcp:sourceFile
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "source file" ;
    rdfs:comment "file:line citation into the real vendored rmcp-2.2.0 (or rmcp-macros-2.2.0) source this pass read directly, relative to that crate's own root (e.g. \"src/handler/server.rs:311-317\")." ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

# ── Properties: rmcp:Macro ──────────────────────────────────────────────

rmcp:macroName
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "macro name" ;
    rdfs:domain rmcp:Macro ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string .

rmcp:macroKind
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "macro kind" ;
    rdfs:comment "\"attribute\" for all 7 -- every one is declared #[proc_macro_attribute] in rmcp-macros/src/lib.rs, confirmed by reading each fn signature directly." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Macro ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:appliesTo
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "applies to" ;
    rdfs:comment "The real syn AST node each macro's implementation parses its `input` TokenStream into: \"fn\" for syn::ImplItemFn (tool, prompt), \"impl\" for syn::ItemImpl (tool_router, tool_handler, prompt_router, prompt_handler, task_handler) -- confirmed by reading each macro's own syn::parse2::<...> call site in rmcp-macros/src/{tool,tool_router,tool_handler,prompt,prompt_router,prompt_handler,task_handler}.rs, not assumed from the doc prose." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Macro ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:macroFields
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "macro fields" ;
    rdfs:comment "Real per-macro attribute fields, `@@`-joined groups of pipe-separated `field|type|usage` (3 columns), transcribed verbatim from each macro's own real `| field | type | usage |` doc table in rmcp-macros/src/lib.rs. Deliberately 3 columns, not clap-noun-verb-pack's cnv:args 4-column `field|rust_type|required|about` shape it otherwise inspired: rmcp-macros' real doc tables carry no \"required\" column at all (every field is optional with a stated default) -- reusing 4 columns here would fabricate a fact the real source does not state. Only the pipe/`@@` delimiter grammar is reused, not the column count. task_handler is the one real exception: its doc comment states one field's semantics in prose, not a table (rmcp-macros/src/lib.rs lines 303-309 have no `| field | type | usage |` markdown at all) -- its macroFields value is still a single field|type|usage group, transcribed from that prose plus the field's real default read from rmcp-macros/src/task_handler.rs, disclosed here as an honest asymmetry, not a template artifact." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Macro ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

# ── Properties: rmcp:Transport ──────────────────────────────────────────

rmcp:transportName
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "transport name" ;
    rdfs:domain rmcp:Transport ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string .

rmcp:transportRole
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "transport role" ;
    rdfs:comment "\"client\", \"server\", or \"helper\" (a generic building block used by both sides, e.g. WorkerTransport, AsyncRwTransport, SinkStreamTransport)." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Transport ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:featureFlag
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "feature flag" ;
    rdfs:comment "The real Cargo feature gating this transport's pub use in src/transport.rs. One real transport (SinkStreamTransport) is unconditionally compiled with no feature gate at all -- its featureFlag value states that fact explicitly (\"(none -- unconditionally compiled, no feature gate)\") rather than being left empty or naming a fake feature." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Transport ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:transportPurpose
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "transport purpose" ;
    rdfs:comment "One real sentence describing the transport, sourced from either README.md's own \"Transport features\" table (for the 5 transports it documents) or src/transport.rs's own module-level doc comment (for WorkerTransport and SinkStreamTransport, which README's table omits but transport.rs's own \"Helper Transport Types\" doc section covers directly)." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Transport ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

# ── Properties: rmcp:Feature ─────────────────────────────────────────────

rmcp:featureName
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "feature name" ;
    rdfs:domain rmcp:Feature ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string .

rmcp:featureDesc
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "feature description" ;
    rdfs:comment "Verbatim one-line description from README.md's own feature tables." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Feature ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:string .

rmcp:featureDefault
    a            rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label   "feature default" ;
    rdfs:comment "true only for the 2 rows README.md's own \"Default\" column marks with a checkmark (server, macros). Cargo.toml's real default array is [\"base64\", \"macros\", \"server\"] -- a third entry, base64, is out of this pass's modeled scope (see ontology header); this property reflects README's own documented defaults, not the full Cargo.toml array." ;
    rdfs:domain  rmcp:Feature ;
    rdfs:range   xsd:boolean .

# ── Individuals: rmcp:HandlerMethod — server (27), src/handler/server.rs ──
