rmcp:server-call-tool
    a rmcp:HandlerMethod ; rmcp:role "server" ; rmcp:methodName "call_tool" ;
    rmcp:paramsType "CallToolRequestParams" ; rmcp:returnType "CallToolResult" ;
    rmcp:defaultBehavior "Returns Err(McpError::method_not_found::<CallToolRequestMethod>()). The method's own real doc comment (lines 283-310) explains a genuine API-design subtlety: Ok(CallToolResult::error(...)) reaches the caller's UI (rendered content), while Err(McpError) is a JSON-RPC protocol error the caller typically cannot read -- almost every \"tool didn't work\" path should return the former, not the latter." ;
    rmcp:sourceFile "src/handler/server.rs:311-317" .

